<title>FRANCE: Usinor Sacilor reaches deal with Atlas Steel.</title>
<headline>Usinor Sacilor reaches deal with Atlas Steel.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>France's Usinor Sacilor said on Tuesday that its Ugine subsidiary had finalised a deal granting Australia's Atlas Steels exclusive distribution rights for flat stainless steel products in Australia and New Zealand.</p>
<p>The deal calls for the creation in Australia of a service center with an annual capacity of 20,000 tonnes, Usinor said in a statement.</p>
<p>Ugine and Atlas Steels will jointly control the capital of the new center.</p>
<p>Atlas Steels is the largest stainless steel distributor in Australia and New Zealand with 14 sites.</p>
<p>Ugine is one of the top producers of flat and long stainless steel products, with plants in France, Thailand and the United States.</p>
